      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(nextcloud-talk,discord): bound response body reads for webhook and error paths",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nTwo unbounded response body reads in bundled plugin HTTP paths can let a hostile endpoint exhaust gateway memory:\n\n1. **extensions/nextcloud-talk/src/bot-preflight.ts** — The error body in `probeNextcloudTalkBotResponseFeature` is read via unbounded `response.text()` when the Nextcloud API returns a non-ok status. The success path already uses `readProviderJsonResponse`.\n\n2. **extensions/discord/src/send.webhook.ts** — The webhook send response is parsed via unbounded `response.json()` on the happy path. The error path already uses bounded `readResponseTextLimited`.\n\n## Changes\n\n1. **extensions/nextcloud-talk/src/bot-preflight.ts** (+4/-1) — Replace unbounded `response.text()` with `readResponseTextLimited(response, 4 KiB)` for the Nextcloud API error body.\n\n2. **extensions/discord/src/send.webhook.ts** (+4/-3) — Replace unbounded `response.json()` with `readProviderJsonResponse(response, \"Discord webhook send\")` for the Discord webhook send response.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- ✅ `pnpm test extensions/nextcloud-talk` — 15 files, 97 tests passed\n- ✅ `pnpm test extensions/discord/src/send.webhook.proxy.test.ts` — 1 file, 7 tests passed\n- ✅ `pnpm tsgo:extensions` — clean\n\nBoth changes follow the same project-wide bound-response-read pattern (#97702, #88401, #97615).\n\n## AI-Assisted\n\nThis PR was AI-assisted.",
